efile` |\n925: | Phase 7 | `grep \"^generate:.*##\" Makefile && grep \"controller-gen\" Makefile` |\n926: | Phase 8 | `grep \"^docker-build:.*##\" Makefile` |\n927: | Phase 9 | `grep \"docker buildx build\" Makefile && grep \"linux/amd64,linux/arm64\" Makefile` |\n928: | Phase 10 | `grep \"kind load docker-image\" Makefile` |\n929: | Phase 11 | `grep \"^e2e:.*##\" Makefile && grep \"./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\" Makefile` |\n930: | Phase 12 | `grep \"^install:.*##\" Makefile && grep \"INSTALL_PREFIX\" Makefile` |\n931: | Phase 13 | `grep \"^clean:.*##\" Makefile && grep \"rm -rf bin/\" Makefile` |\n932: | Phase 14 | `grep \"^help:.*##\" Makefile && grep \"awk.*##\" Makefile` |\n933: | Phase 15 | `make --dry-run help 2>/dev/null` |\n934: | Phase 16 | `make build && ls bin/workloadmanager` |\n935: | Phase 17 | `make test-coverage && test -f coverage.out` |\n936: | Phase 18 | `make lint` |\n937: | Phase 19 | `make docker-build-all IMAGE_REPO=test VERSION=test` |\n938: | Phase 20 | `make clean && test ! -d bin/` |\n939: | Phase 21 | `make help | grep \"Build\"` |\n940: | Phase 22 | `make build VERSION=test-override BINDIR=test-bin` |\n941: \n942: ---\n943: \n944: ## Acceptance Criteria\n945: \n946: - [ ] Makefile has all 9 variable definitions (IMAGE_REPO, VERSION, TARGETOS, TARGETARCH, BINDIR, GO_VERSION, GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION, CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION, INSTALL_PREFIX)\n947: - [ ] Makefile has all 7 binary build targets (workloadmanager, router, picod, agentd, agentctl, agentcube, agentsandbox)\n948: - [ ] Makefile has 4 cross-compile targets (linux-amd64, linux-arm64, darwin-amd64, darwin-arm64)\n949: - [ ] Makefile has test, test-coverage, test-race targets\n950: - [ ] Makefile has fmt, vet, lint, gen-check, gen-copyright targets\n951: - [ ] Makefile has generate, gen-crd, gen-client, gen-all targets\n952: - [ ] Makefile has docker-build, docker-build-router, docker-build-picod, docker-build-all targets\n953: - [ ] Makefile has docker-buildx-push, docker-buildx-push-router, docker-buildx-push-picod targets\n954: - [ ] Makefile has kind-load, kind-load-router, kind-load-picod, kind-load-all targets\n955: - [ ] Makefile has e2e, e2e-setup, e2e-clean targets\n956: - [ ] Makefile has install and 7 install-* targets\n957: - [ ] Makefile has clean, clean-bin, clean-test targets\n958: - [ ] Makefile has help target with awk formatter\n959: - [ ] All targets have ## documentation comments\n960: - [ ] Categories marked with ##@ headers (Build, Test, Quality, Docker, E2E, Codegen, Install)\n961: - [ ] SHELL set to bash with pipefail\n962: - [ ] .NOTPARALLEL for docker-build-all\n963: - [ ] go-install-tool macro for tool installation\n964: - [ ] make build produces all 7 binaries\n965: - [ ] make test runs unit tests\n966: - [ ] make test-coverage generates coverage.out and coverage.html\n967: - [ ] make docker-build-all builds all 3 images\n968: - [ ] make help displays formatted help screen\n969: - [ ] Variable overrides work (VERSION, IMAGE_REPO, BINDIR)\n970: \n971: ---\n972: \n973: ## File Changes Summary\n974: \n975: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n976: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n977: | `Makefile` | Modify | ~250 | Expand from 71 lines to full build system with all targets |\n978: \n979: ---\n980: \n981: ## Implementation Notes\n982: \n983: ### Help Target Pattern\n984: \n985: ```makefile\n986: help: ## Display this help screen\n987: \t@awk 'BEGIN {FS = \":.*##\"; printf \"\\nUsage:\\n  make <target>\\n\\n\"} \\\n988: \t\t/^##@/ { category = substr($$0, 4); printf \"%-20s\\n\", category } \\\n989: \t\t/^[%a-zA-Z0-9_-]+:.*##/ { target = substr($$1, 1, length($$1)-1); \\\n990: \t\tprintf \"  %-20s %s\\n\", target, substr($$0, index($$0, \"##\") + 3) } \\\n991: \t\tEND { printf \"\\n\" }' $(MAKEFILE_LIST)\n992: ```\n993: \n994: ### go-install-tool Macro\n995: \n996: ```makefile\n997: define go-install-tool\n998: @[ -f \"$(1)\" ] || { \\\n999: set -e ; \\\n1000: echo \"Installing $(2)\" ; \\\n1001: GOBIN=$(LOCALBIN) go install $(2)@$(3) ; }\n1002: endef\n1003: ```\n1004: \n1005: ### Binary Build Pattern\n1006: \n1007: ```makefile\n1008: build-workloadmanager: generate ## Build workloadmanager binary only\n1009: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n1010: ```\n1011: \n1012: ### Docker Build Pattern\n1013: \n1014: ```makefile\n1015: docker-build: ## Build workloadmanager Docker image\n1016: \tdocker build \\\n1017: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n1018: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION) \\\n1019: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=$(TARGETOS) \\\n1020: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=$(TARGETARCH) \\\n1021: \t\t.\n1022: ```\n1023: \n1024: ### Cross-Compile Pattern\n1025: \n1026: ```makefile\n1027: build-linux-amd64: generate ## Build for Linux AMD64\n1028: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n1029: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n1030: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n1031: ```\n1032: \n1033: ---\n1034: \n1035: ## Implementation Timeline\n1036: \n1037: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n1038: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n1039: | Phase 1: Variable System | T1.1-T1.9 | Pending | 0% |\n1040: | Phase 2: Build Targets | T2.1-T2.10 | Pending | 0% |\n1041: | Phase 3: Individual Binary Targets | T3.1-T3.8 | Pending | 0% |\n1042: | Phase 4: Cross-Compile Targets | T4.1-T4.4 | Pending | 0% |\n1043: | Phase 5: Test Targets | T5.1-T5.8 | Pending | 0% |\n1044: | Phase 6: Quality Targets | T6.1-T6.13 | Pending | 0% |\n1045: | Phase 7: Codegen Targets | T7.1-T7.9 | Pending | 0% |\n1046: | Phase 8: Docker Build Targets | T8.1-T8.10 | Pending | 0% |\n1047: | Phase 9: Docker Multi-Arch | T9.1-T9.9 | Pending | 0% |\n1048: | Phase 10: Kind Load Targets | T10.1-T10.6 | Pending | 0% |\n1049: | Phase 11: E2E Targets | T11.1-T11.8 | Pending | 0% |\n1050: | Phase 12: Install Targets | T12.1-T12.12 | Pending | 0% |\n1051: | Phase 13: Clean Targets | T13.1-T13.7 | Pending | 